HEADWORD: Ant-cattle
<hw>Ant"-cat`tle</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Various kinds of plant lice or aphids tended by
ants for the sake of the honeydew which they secrete; plural of <er>ant
cow</er>. See <er>Aphips</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ant cow</ent>⟦br⟧
